The Management to consider the following to improve the water system operation:

1.  Review the water rates presently adopted by the Municipality;

2. Identify strategy in improving its collection efficiency to at least 95% of its monthly billing.  A daily or weekly basis of collection might be considered or introduce  an early payment discount;

3. Maintain a Special Account wherein income from water system will be kept intact and adopt a policy that the income therein will be used for its operation; and lastly,

4.  Include in the report the consumption of different offices in order to measure correctly the result of operation of the water system.

To sustain the market operation we are recommending that management consider the following:

1.  Review the rate of its rental considering the cost of its construction and revisit the provision on its tariff as embodied in its revenue code;

2.  Create an atmosphere which is conducive to the active utilization of the market area so that economic activity is improved, which will in turn encourage the business sector to locate their businesses in the area.  Management might consider having a designated market day and requiring the trading of its rubber production at the market site.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor, as provided by COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 25, 2015, require the coordination and cooperation of the following personnel:
Local Accountant
Prepare the Journal Voucher to record the beginning balance of the road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Networks Ledger Card (Annex D), respectively;
Support the JEV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, working paper on the distribution of costs for the road components, and working paper on the determination of the depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;
Keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and components for every network ;and
Prepare lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each component at the end of the year;
Municipal Treasurer/General Services
Maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map;
Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components (Annex E).
Municipal Engineer
Provide the local accountant and the general services officer with the complete 	description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.
